The paper deals with coded caching schemes in wireless networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the tradeoff between transmission amount and computation complexity, which is a topic related to systems and control (cs.SI). The paper proposes new constructions for coded caching schemes, which is a topic related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
